Ughhh I feel terrible, my throad and nose and HEAD!!!!! I can't stop caughing or blowing my nose. And tomorrow I have to go to school so that I can go to the EC and finish my phelpstival story and start a new one. And I have to do my voice over, and my throat is just feeling terrible. I'm going to take tea to school and when i go to the EC im going to drink coffee. The pressure is on for college apps and all that other shit. I cant even fill out apps b/c I dont have my SAT scores. I didn't even take A SAT. So I'm going to try and do my essays and I'm going to ask Mr.Hain and Ms. Gundlach to write me reccomendations. And I'm probably going to ask Cindy too. My 5 colleges are down- the ones I'm applying to. They are Edinboro, NMU, La Salle, Ithaca, and Marist. 2 are in NY 2 are in PA and 1 is in Michigan. I really want to get like a short Halle Berry haircut but my dad wont let me b/c he says I will look ugly, and that people pay to have my hair and that my head is too big anyway. Oh well, hmm- what else is new. I'm still dieting!!!! I don't even have the urge to cheat when i'm feeling down or sad, stressed, or frustrated. And I used to go straight to food to help me. Now I'm just like there is not point, I'll regret it afterwards anyway and that regret is just going to add to my stress. I just need to start exercising and if my plan goes the way I want it to, I will start to go to a gym if/when I get my license at the end of this month. So that this way I have no excuse not to go, I can just drive myself there. And next month I'll probably start applying to jobs and things like that. But right now i should be doing some research for the AIDs/HIV awareness club. Finding some organizions we can go and help out and things like that. So I'm going to do that this weekend. In addition to my college essay, regular HW, and trying to read most of this Virginia Woolf book so that I can start on Beowolf. The pressure is already starting to come on. But I think i can handle it, I believe I have gotten stronger as the years have gone by and there are times I just wish I could drop dead, not like suicide, but just die from exhaustion, but int he end it always works out. My main goals now are to loose weight, do well in my internship and school, finish all my college shit and hopefully ( with God's help) get a scholarship. If I can do all of this and in the meantimme keep a job, help the HIV club, and my bro. I will have sucessfully juggeled a shit load of work. I think I can do it, I just hope God will help me through. The rest is up to me. Okay well I'm going to go take some more medicine, and READ!! Ciao

Well, it has been a very long and stressful week. I slept as if i were a bear going into hybernation yesterday. my intersnhip is going well , and my taping went bad. lol. I kept on messing up, but when i saw the end result my performance was nice especially compared to my co-anchor, who didn't have to do as many re-dos as I did. the only problem was that my hair was poofy and i looked fat, but my face looked cute, lol. so next time i will NOT straighten my hair when it is raining and i wil NOT wear that black top on camera. I will also read SLOWLY to prevent stumbling. My first story is the Phelpstival, which is today. Um also today is the 3rd? anniversary of the Sept. 11th attacks and Ethiopian New Year. I took a practice ACT at Sylvan and got a 23.25, and last time I got a 22. So I'm thinking I should just focus on my SATs, i think those will really help me get a scholarship. Even though my ACT score is above average- most colleges want like a 27 for a scholarship where as for SATs you need like a 1275, and I  have a 1150, so i just need to get an extra 12-13 questions right or skip that many. Hmm what else, oh yea I have so many things to do! I need to write a draft proposal for a Dec. 1st concert for HIV/AIDs awareness with NO help from my club advisor. I also need to start researching essay topics colleges want and think about and begin to write. And I need to buy snacks for the first meeting and buy books for English. I just want this month to be over so I understand my schduel. Then I can contact the IOCC and see if I can do some volunteer work there and then find a weekend job. And around the 27th I'm going to take my driver's test. There is so much going on right now. It feels good and it also feels overwhelming. I'm also going to join a gym , it will help me gain energy and loose weight. Alrighty then I'm going to try and finish all the things on my list. Ciao

Well it's Labor Day weekend, and for some odd reason i've been wanting to studt lately. I think it has finally hit me that I'm a senior and I have to start applying to colleges soon , so that that means keep up grades and a good SAT score. Today I went to Sylvan ( like every saturday morning ) and guess what!?!?!?! I got a 1150!!!!! I improved 100 points from last week. My goal is to get a 1250, but i mean its only 50 points away from a 1300... so I'm really going to try and study. Look over some vocab and expecially math. Oh yea this monday I started taking this diet pill called Xenadrine, and I think it's really going to help me lose weight. I have been reading reviews of it and people have lost so much weight. The thing is that they also exercise, which I have NOT been doing. I think I should get my lazy, fat ass up and start doing that. Go back to my running thing. So the monday I started the date was August the 30th, so when I tell people how much I lost, i can tell them when I started dieting! Hmm what else has happened, I feel so overwhelmed with this whole college and SAT shit, I feel like i'll have a panic attack or heart attack everytime I thikn about it. what if i cant get a scholarship? I know i'll get accepted- i have great grades and w/e. But i'm really searching for a scholarship. the thing that sucks though is that Maryland has like no colleges with a broadcast journalism major. so this means i cant even visit the college i'll be attending b/c it's probably far. So I got an e-mail from Ms.Lorenze ( my EC advisor) and she said I'd be on camera on thursday , NOT Wednesday- which is when she told me, w/e. thats cool with me- i just have to tell people the date has changed. I'm such a freak, i already have my outfits picked for next week. you know what i have noticed about myself, i'm very forgetful. my sister told me to wake her up for work at 9 a.m. and I FORGOT!!!!!!! I feel and felt so bad. and now she is putting this guilt shit on me saying that she might get fired ( b/c this was her first day). i already feel enough guilt. UGHHHH! So besides completely negating the feeling of being smart today  I cut my bro's hair- AND it actually looks good. I got a new ringtone ( Where is the Love-BEP) and a wallpaper ( The Ethiopian and American Flag and my pic in the middle). And tomorrow there is a church picnic. I'm reserving Monday for a study/ homework day. I really want to do well, and with God's help, my family's support, and my determination- I know I can do it. Ciao!

Today was the first day of school..... I was excited like a dork for some reason. I think its just because for the first time, I'm really happy with the classes I'm taking. I'm ready to learn and absorb. The odd thing is that, all my teachers are men... hehe... not that I mind, it's just that I've never had that before.
First Period: AP English - Mr. Letsch ( Man )
Second Period: Forensics Honors- Mr. Filosa ( Man )
Third Period: Economics Honors- Mr.Goodman (Man)
Fourth Period: Trig/Algebra- Mr. Zeller ( Yummy Man )
Fifth Period: U.S. History honors- Mr. Bickerstaff ( Yummy Italian Man)
So you see, all these men are going to be in my face distracting me especially b/c 4/5 of my teachers are not married. I know its wronge, but I cannot help it. I like my men like my wine- mature, ripe, and imported!!!!! lol. I start my internship at the EC September 7th, NEXT WEEK! And I start on-camera September 8th, NEXT WEEK! I alreayd have my outfit planned out of course. Oh yea, I have started an SAT Prep course at Sylvan Learning Center- I have already improved my schore by 75 points. Im shooting for like a 1250- I'll be sure to get a scholarship with that at NMU!!! My dream college, although far I think it will be a great experience. OKay well responsibility beckons...Ciao

YAY! this wednesday im going shopping again. then thursday is 6 flags, then friday is jewlery shopping. and saturday my parents are coming. but friday i have to go to work with my sis which will suck b/c she works overnight. but w.e. okay well im waiting for my toenails to dry. ciao

Wow, I never realized so much in the past few days how much I do and how unapreciated I am. I do so fucking much for this family and all I get is being scolded by the stupid bitch who gave birth to me. I not only have school work and problems of my own but I also have to take care of my brother's illness , watch him, and help him with his HW and make sure all his papers are signed and up to date. It doesn't help that he goes to a Catholic School, there is so much more to do! I have to make meals, fix my fathers bed , make appointments , tell people when to go food shopping. And to top it all off my sister and I are still not talking which means I have added work. No one ever helps me with my brother. For an example, yesterday morning, I fixed my father breakfast again and I also had to fix my brothers , make sure he had all his medicine supplies and his regular book bag in order. And I had to give him his medicine. Both my father and mother saw how stressed I was and instead of helping, my father sits there and says how great of a daughter I am and my mother watches me like the retard she is. I am stuck on the decision of whether or not I should run for class president. I want to and Im pretty sure I'll win but it will probably be more added stress since I'm going to intern, be president of the HIV/AIDs Awareness club and still deal w/ the shit I do now. It's so pathetic. I don't even know how I'm supposed to go to Ethiopia this summer with that woman who gave birth to me. If I cant get along with her here , then how am I supposed to in a completely different country.I'm seriously thinking of getting into another big fight with her so that we can ignore eachother again. At least then I would have less stress. OMG! I just remembered, I have been asking people to take my bro and I to the library so that I can get him a fairytale book for his project due tomorrow. And no one takes us. It turned out find b/c I got a book from the internet to print out. But it was so stressful b/c he is getting a cold and he wasn't focusing and following directions so the project took so much longer then it should have. I don't know what I am going to do with my life. Suicide is so over-rated. I just want to run away. Get the fuck out of this place. I'm going crazy!! Tomorrow is Friday... I need to do some mega shopping. I need pens,pencils, make an appointment to get a new eye prescription, mascara, batteries, crayons , paper , socks , and shit load of other things I can't remember right now. I cheated today, which is no surprise since I'm addicted to food. And it is a way that I releave stress and get some comfort. I excercised, but not as much as I wanted too. I am getting terrible back pains. I completely failed a Chem test I took today. God willing , my life will change for the better soon. I just need to go to church...Ciao... I'll leave you with something inspirational by Gary Zukav
"Feel your intentions in your heart. Feel not what your mind tells you, but what your heart tells you."

So I've been exercising a lot lately,my ass is on FIRE!The whole day at school my ass has been hurting. But!!! I have been cheating on my diet. It's soooo hard. But I'm eating less and less carbs each day. I heard something about Dr. Atkins and the reason for his death , I dunno i gotta research it. They are probably trying to say the Atkins diet is not healthy. WHICH, it is! I started the diet, off and on before a lot of people knew about it. About 5 years ago, in the 6th grade.
